        <section class="mt-4">
            <h3>Implications of Digital Inequality</h3>
            <p>
                The lack of reliable internet in rural areas has far-reaching consequences, including:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>Economic Impact:</strong> Limited internet access restricts rural businesses from 
                    competing in digital markets and reduces opportunities for innovation.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Educational Disparities:</strong> Students in rural areas struggle with online learning 
                    due to poor connectivity, widening the education gap.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Healthcare Access:</strong> Telemedicine, which requires high-speed internet, 
                    is often unavailable in remote regions.
                </li>
            </ul>
